t: "O believers! When the believing women come to you as emigrants,¬†test their intentions‚ÄĒtheir faith¬†is best known to Allah‚ÄĒand if you find them to be believers, then do not send them back to the disbelievers. These ňĻwomenňļ are not lawful ňĻwivesňļ for the disbelievers, nor are the disbelievers lawful ňĻhusbandsňļ for them. ňĻButňļ repay the disbelievers whatever ňĻdowriesňļ they had paid. And there is no blame on you if you marry these ňĻwomenňļ as long as you pay them their dowries. And do not hold on to marriage with polytheistic women.¬†ňĻButňļ demand ňĻrepayment ofňļ whatever ňĻdowriesňļ you had paid, and let the disbelievers do the same. That is the judgment of Allah‚ÄĒHe judges between you. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"